      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEM N EM NZ (2) left New Zealand off a win and started for David Micallef the same way, coming from the back row to get home narrowly last week at Bathurst. Up in grade but the good draw can see her take the next step. EMERGING DEAL (4) will find this easier than her last attempt in the Gold Bracelet final and she went into that series off a win at Canberra. Has won at this circuit and distance before so looks well placed. VIEW THE ART (9) led and stuck on for a 1.2m third here eight days ago. Owns a decent record at this circuit and distance and draws for a trail. VINCHESKA (8) draws wide but must be respected having scored two wins and a close second from her last three starts.",
